        "synopsis": {
            "value": "When Jeong Ji-An (Kim Hye-Jun) was little, her mother was murdered by her father and her father\ntook his own life on the day of her grandmother's funeral. Jung Ji-An was suddenly left all alone. Her uncle, Jeong Jin-Man (Lee Dong-Wook), took her in and they lived together. While raising Jeong Ji-An, Jeong Jin-Man ran a mysterious shopping mall. Jeong Ji-An eventually enrolled in a university and left her uncle's home. She began to live by herself. One day, Jeong Ji-An hears that her uncle has suddenly passed away. She goes back to her uncle's home, where she lived with him. She becomes to know about the real identity of the shopping mall that Jeong Jin-Man ran.",
            "source": "asianwiki",
            "source_link": "https://asianwiki.com/A_Shop_for_Killers"
